   <titles>
      <title>Same Orientation: Explanation</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>Wait a minute! If we want to test whether two ordered bases <math>
                     <latex>\EuScript{B}</latex>
                  </math> and <math>
                     <latex>\EuScript{C}</latex>
                  </math> determine the same or opposite orientations of <math>
                     <latex>V</latex>
                  </math>, how do we know whether we need to convert from <math>
                     <latex>\EuScript{B}</latex>
                  </math>-coordinates to <math>
                     <latex>\EuScript{C}</latex>
                  </math>-coordinates or vice versa?</para.body>
            </para>
            <para>
               <para.body>Answer: It does not matter! The determinants of both matrices have the same sign. To see this, we just need to recall that </para.body>
            </para>
            <math.display>
               <latex>C_{\EuScript{B}\EuScript{C}} = \left( C_{\EuScript{C}\EuScript{B}} \right)^{-1}</latex>
            </math.display>
            <para>
               <para.body>Because then we compute</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.array column="3">
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>+1</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>=</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>\det( C_{\EuScript{B}\EuScript{C}}) \cdot \det( C_{\EuScript{B} \EuScript{C}} )^{-1}</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row rowspan="1">
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex/>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>=</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
                  <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                     <math>
                        <latex>\det( C_{\EuScript{B}\EuScript{C}}) \cdot \det( C_{\EuScript{C} \EuScript{B}} )</latex>
                     </math>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </math.array>
            <para>
               <para.body>So the two matrices have the same sign.</para.body>
            </para>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </body>
